com.rawva.structures.graphs

Interface Graph.Edge<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of elements in this edge
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DirectedEdge, UndirectedEdge
    Enclosing interface:
    Graph<V>

    public static interface Graph.Edge<V>
    An edge is a pair of objects (o1, o2), signifying some association between o1 and o2. o1 is called the tail of the edge, and o2 is called the head.
    Author:
    Raymond Tang
